# Project Structure & Code Organization

- **Respect the existing structure**: This project has an `agent/` (Python backend) and `frontend/` (React) layout. Add new code in the appropriate area.
- **Avoid monolithic files**: Split logic into focused modules. Extract reusable logic into hooks, utilities, or shared components instead of bloating single files.
- **Minimal, targeted changes**: When editing, change only what’s necessary. Don’t refactor unrelated code unless explicitly requested.
- **Organized additions**: Put new components under `frontend/src/components/`, API routes under `frontend/api/`, agent logic under `agent/src/`, and utilities in dedicated modules.
